        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 8:22AM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>A few pockets of dense fog are being reported across portions of
northern El Paso County this morning, mainly confined to the
Palmer Divide. A quick reduction in visibility to under one-
quarter of a mile is likely when encountering the denser fog.

When traveling, be prepared for rapidly fluctuating visibilities
in short distances. Use your low beam settings on your vehicles
headlights and allow for plenty of distance between you and the
vehicle in front of you.
</description>
